Keep up the good work! The next topic we will cover is functions. Functions are sections of code that execute other code and make it reusable. 
In ES6 there are 2 main ways to declare a function, the function keyword and arrow functions.
 Syntax: function name(params) {
   code
} 
Task 12: Declare a function using the respective keyword that when given 2 numbers will add them together, then print out the result. The number pairs you need to test are 1+2, 10+15, 100+400
